A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 26, 2025, as Charter Schools Day at the state capitol; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Georgia's first charter school law was enacted in 1993, and there are currently
4 96 charter schools operating in communities throughout the state; and
5 WHEREAS, charter schools are tuition-free, public schools that have fair and open
6 enrollment procedures and serve students and families in all 159 counties in Georgia; and
7 WHEREAS, a recent national study of charter school performance conducted by the Center
8 for Research on Education Outcomes at Stanford University found that students in charter
9 schools outperformed their peers in traditional public schools by an average of 16 additional
10 days of learning in reading and six additional days of learning in math; and
11 WHEREAS, the members of this body commend the dedicated teachers and leaders serving
12 in Georgia's charter schools and celebrate the 65,000 public school students enrolled in
13 charter schools throughout the state; and
